  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "As discussed with @cwhinfrey, @jamesyoung and @spalladino, it'd be interesting to include a factory such as [archanova's](https://github.com/archanova/solidity/blob/08f8f6bedc6e71c24758d20219b7d0749d75919d/contracts/contractCreator/ContractCreator.sol) (by @stanislaw-glogowski, which uses CREATE2, making it possible to predict the contract's address) into OpenZeppelin, possibly expanding upon it to cover more use cases.\r\n\r\nOne aspect in particular I'd like to discuss is constructor arguments: the linked implementation has a fixed bytecode, but it shouldn't be too difficult to come up with a scheme where these initial values are injected.",
